en_7978096_0	The Water Supply and Drainage Board says that a water cut will come into effect in the Gampaha District from 8 a.m. to 5  p.m. on Sunday.
en_7978096_1	Thereby, the nine hour water cut will be implemented in areas that fall under the Kelaniya, Wattala, Hendela.
en_7978096_2	Biyagama, Mahara Pradeshiya Sabhas and also in areas that belong to the Dompe Pradeshiya Sabha such as Deketana, Namaluwe, Kalukodhayawa and Dompe.
en_7978096_3	In addition the water cut will also come into effect in Peliyagoda, Wattala and Ja-ela areas that fall under the purview of the Katunayake – Seeduwa Urban Council.
en_7978096_4	The Water Supply and Drainage Board further notes that the a water cut will be implemented from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. on Sunday in the Biyagama Investment Zone as well.
en_7978096_5	The water cut will be implemented on Sunday, as a result of a disruption of power supply to the Biyagama refinery.
